<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Li, ZZ" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="526 - 539" refId="B42" refString="Wei, LM, Yang, ZH, 2007. Sarcophagidae. In: Li, ZZ, Yang, MF, Jin, DC, Eds., Insects from Leigongshan Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 526 - 539" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Leigongshan Landscape." year="2007">Wei and Yang (2007)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. autochthona" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="autochthona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. autochthona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as close to 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. (Pseudothyrsocnema) caudagalli" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="caudagalli" subGenus="Pseudothyrsocnema">S. (Pseudothyrsocnema) caudagalli</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Böttcher">Boettcher</normalizedToken>
, 1912, but we are here proposing a synonymy with 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. (L.) kanoi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="kanoi" subGenus="L.">S. (L.) kanoi</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Li, ZZ" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="526 - 539" refId="B42" refString="Wei, LM, Yang, ZH, 2007. Sarcophagidae. In: Li, ZZ, Yang, MF, Jin, DC, Eds., Insects from Leigongshan Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 526 - 539" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Leigongshan Landscape." year="2007">Wei and Yang (2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 72) illustrated the phallus of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. autochthona" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="autochthona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. autochthona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having a short, arm-like extension arising from the left lateral part of the distiphallus (probably the proximal part of the juxta) and a long, slender, process arising from the right lateral part of the distiphallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Sarcophaga (Liosarcophaga) kanoi Park, 1962; phallus, lateral view A adapted from Lehrer (2012) B adapted from Wei &amp; Yang (2007, as Pierretia autochthona)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.83267.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706071" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">6</figureCitation>
). We consider this apparent asymmetry to be an artefact, and possibly an inaccuracy of the original illustration. This could not be confirmed because the holotype of 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. autochthona" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="autochthona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. autochthona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, deposited in CDCP, has not been available for study through ordinary loan.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.83267.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706071" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Figure 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Park" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga (Liosarcophaga) kanoi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kanoi" subGenus="Liosarcophaga">Sarcophaga (Liosarcophaga) kanoi</taxonomicName>
Park, 1962; phallus, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">A</emphasis>
adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Lehrer, AZ" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica, Bari" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="3 - 158" refId="B16" refString="Lehrer, AZ, 2012. Taxonomic Atlas of the postabdominal structures Sarcophagidae (Insecta, Diptera) Vol. II. Entomologica, Bari 44: 3 - 158" title="Taxonomic Atlas of the postabdominal structures Sarcophagidae (Insecta, Diptera) Vol. II." volume="44" year="2012">Lehrer (2012)</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">B</emphasis>
adapted from Wei &amp; Yang (2007, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pierretia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pierretia autochthona" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="autochthona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pierretia autochthona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
